  "caption": "A contemporary pop ballad, polished and emotionally driven, building from an intimate piano-and-vocal opening to a huge, glossy chorus. Warm piano and soft synth pads carry the verses over a deep, rounded bass and subtle electronic textures. A bright, clear female pop vocal — breathy and close in the verses, belting and soaring in the choruses — with heavily layered, stacked harmonies on the hook. The beat builds from sparse finger-snaps and soft programmed percussion into a punchy modern pop groove with a driving backbeat; shimmering synths, lush strings, and a wall of background vocals lift the final chorus into an anthemic, stadium-pop climax before dropping to a bare, vulnerable outro. Crisp, radio-ready production with wide dynamic range. Bittersweet but uplifting — heartbreak wrapped in a singalong hook.",
  "global_caption": "",
  "lyrics": "[Verse 1 ]\nWe made our vows to build this life\nFull of fire, full of promise, full of pride\nA pledge of union under a big star sky\nSigns I couldn't see, things only love could hide\n\n[Pre-Chorus ]\nI didn't ask where the land came from\nI didn't ask whose bones were in the ground\nIn this love I didn't want to look far down\n\n[Chorus]\nYou are the love of my life, always stood by your side\nRaised our children in your house\nEach one is equal under God\nBut the fighting never stops\nYou choose the worst of what you are\nWhat I fell in love with feels so far\n\n[Verse 2- drums hit hard]\nYou built the railroads on the backs of men\nWhipped the soul to squeez the green from flesh\nBut you'd turn around and be so generous\nI told myself great men are allowed some shame\nPut the cover-up on the bruise you made\n\n[Chorus ]\nYou are the love of my life, always stood by your side\nRaised our children in your house\nEach one is equal under God\nBut the fighting never stops\nYou choose the worst of what you are\nWhat I fell in love with feels so far\n\n[Verse 3 - Strings enter]\nThere were the moments that you made me proud\nOur house together standing out\nWe were the symbol for all our friends\nThat a union could endure and never end\n\n[Pre-Chorus]\nI know the demons never left you\nLiving somewhere behind your eyes\nFind an enemy to distract you\nFrom a house you filled with lies\n\n[Chorus - Full band swell, powerful vocals]\nYOU ARE THE LOVE OF MY LIFE, ALWAYS STOOD BY YOUR SIDE\nRaised our children in your house\nall men are equal under God\nbut the fighting never stops\nyou Choose the worst of what you are\nthe country I fell in love with Feels so far\n\n[Outro]\nI still believe in what you could be\nI have that faith somewhere deep in me\nBut faith without a partner is an American tragedy \n(ooh)\nan American tragedy ",
